      "description": "<p>As a Principal Engineer, you will join Google Cloud Compute Site Reliability Engineering. You will provide executive-level technical leadership for a large organization that is responsible for reliable operation, engineering, and evolution of Google's Cloud Compute offerings. You'll be a deep technical expert and an exceptional leader, influencing projects and delivering a complex technical roadmap across multiple organizations/teams. </p><div><br></div><div>In this role, you will create the reality of a stable and trustworthy cloud computing platform for a diverse pool of customers and workloads worldwide. You'll balance feature velocity with reliability and cost efficiency.\nYou will partner with a wide and diverse array of teams working in the Google Cloud Compute space (e.g., Site Reliability Engineering and Development) to set the technical direction for compute reliability.\nYou'll constantly challenge our approach and goals to elevate our platform reliability beyond our current capabilities.\nYou will contribute to our most complex technical projects and externally visible product decisions, using your technical acumen, problem-solving abilities, and good judgment to help build scalable and future-proof Google systems.\n\n</div><p>Google Cloud accelerates organizations’ ability to digitally transform their business with the best infrastructure, platform, industry solutions and expertise. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology – all on the cleanest cloud in the industry. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.</p>",
