      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Work with Engineering teams to facilitate part number creation and ensure the build of materials (BOM) are released and aligned with the product life cycle management (PLM) and Contract Manufacturer's BOM.</li>\n<li>Manage the product Build Matrix (system configuration decoder). Ensure material procurement and CTB (Clear to Build), tracking engineering parallel paths and investigations, and product configurations.</li>\n<li>Lead asset management build readiness meeting with Contract Manufacturing to drive ship to file (S2F) and allocation deliverables.</li>\n<li>Manage product labeling and build documentation. Maintain product allocation database and work with Contract Manufacturing, Logistics, and Distribution teams to ensure timely distribution to all product groups.\n</li>\n<li>Analyze and balance inventory asset to ensure and minimize risk for the Engineering team's testing/development.\n</li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience.</li>\n<li>2 years of experience in new hardware development.\n</li>\n<li>2 years of experience in consumer hardware development.</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Experience with hardware BOM structures, changing control concepts, and PDM/PLM tools (e.g., Agile, Team center).</li>\n<li>Familiar with hardware development and manufacturing processes, vendor relations and working with Contract Manufacturers (CM) in Asia.</li>\n<li>Proven ability to work and thrive in a fast paced and time sensitive environment and to effectively prioritize when working on multiple tasks/projects.</li>\n<li>Ability to manage spreadsheets and coordinate across cross-functional teams and job functions.</li>\n<li>Excellent written/verbal communication, organizational, and multitasking skills.</li>\n<li>Ability to speak and write in English and Mandarin fluently.</li>\n</ul>",
