      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Lead analysis of systems across identity, safety, security, and privacy domains to identify opportunities for integration and alignment.</li>\n<li>Lead development of roadmaps for paths across technical stacks.</li>\n<li>Work with cross-functional leadership of the identity, safety, security, and privacy domains to get alignment on the roadmaps and enable execution against those.</li>\n<li>Help lead the execution against strategy for some critical projects and areas, partnering with relevant engineering and cross-functional directors.</li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, a related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.</li>\n<li>15 years of experience working as a technical software engineering leader or 13 years with an advanced degree.</li>\n<li>Experience with distributed systems.</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Experience motivating others by creating a sense of vision or purpose, creating a vision for the future, communicating clearly, and employing a collaborative leadership approach.</li>\n<li>Experience in identity, privacy, safety, or security domains, and experience leading cross-functional engineering projects.</li>\n<li>Ability to provide clarity and alignment across the organization on goals, outcomes, and timelines.</li>\n<li>Ability to take an entrepreneurial and strategic approach and work within technology and business.</li>\n<li>Ability to lead a distributed team of engineers across organizations and core teams, and encourage engineering excellence and mentor the team to uphold it.</li>\n</ul>",
