      "description": "<p><b></b></p>\n<p>At Google, we follow a simple but vital premise: \"Focus on the user and all else will follow.\" Through our growth marketing programs, we help customers meet their business objectives more efficiently and effectively with Google Ads. As a Growth Engineer, you will work on critical services and applications to accelerate ads growth and marketing programs, and help the transition to a more automated future. </p><p>As a Growth Engineer, your work will be end-to-end to architect and implement our front-end interactive UIs and integrate with back-end systems. You will implement interactive, scalable, and localized modern UIs and experiences across devices to help build out site personalization and content recommendation to the number of properties we support. </p><p>In this role, you will be required to design and implement backend microservices, extend Content Management System (CMS) features, and other infrastructure components that store and ingest data from client-provided data, APIs, and internal back-end data sources. You will develop interactive interfaces, front-ends, prototypes, and web-based products, including server-side implementation.</p><p><br><br></p><p>Google is an engineering company at heart. We hire people with a broad set of technical skills who are ready to take on some of technology's greatest challenges and make an impact on users around the world. At Google, engineers not only revolutionize search, they routinely work on scalability and storage solutions, large-scale applications and entirely new platforms for developers around the world. From Google Ads to Chrome, Android to YouTube, social to local, Google engineers are changing the world one technological achievement after another.</p>",
