      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Ensure that Google Ads services have reliability and uptime appropriate to users’ needs and a fast rate of improvement while staying mindful of capacity and performance. \n</li>\n<li>Build creative engineering solutions to operations and infrastructure problems, focusing on optimizing existing systems, building infrastructure, and eliminating work through automation. Determine how our systems relate to each other and use a breadth of tools and approaches to solve a variety of problems. \n</li>\n<li>Build a culture of diversity, intellectual curiosity, problem-solving, and openness. \n</li>\n<li>Manage, innovate, and create designs for software that drives improvements to the availability, scalability, latency, and efficiency of Google’s Advertising products and/or services.\n</li>\n<li>Work cross-functionally with product area leads to guide product engineering, and collaborate with Ads feature developers.\n</li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in computer science or equivalent practical experience.\n</li>\n<li>15 years of experience in engineering and technical development.\n</li>\n<li>Experience working across organizational boundaries, building relationships, and importing and exporting ideas.</li>\n<li>Experience with technical leadership.</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Experience working in Google Products or one of the services in the Product ecosystem, or experience with a technical infrastructure outside of Google with similar scope.</li>\n<li>Experience with SRE or DevOps.\n</li>\n<li>Expertise in data structures, algorithms, and analysis.</li>\n<li>Expertise in analyzing and troubleshooting distributed systems.\n</li>\n<li>Ability to understand the relationship between the organization and its environment, identify connections, adopt different perspectives, and quickly respond to changing circumstances.\n</li>\n<li>Excellent critical thinking, analytical, problem-solving, and organizational skills, with outstanding written and verbal communication skills.</li>\n</ul>",
