      "id": "75925055579529926",
      "title": "Principal Engineer, Tech Lead, Analytical Storage",
      "categories": [
        "SOFTWARE_ENGINEERING"
      ],
      "apply_url": "https://www.google.com/about/careers/applications/signin?jobId=CiUAL2FckcQXAaT0A7D9D5G5vwmEFPN6U38L4W7tC-zRYnITXocZEjsAkXGnOwKMyLQyXTE6VfXKfeww5vGUtFmD9N0iWg7AtjYumgGhYBZ8vsphZNNk23PTZkt4__aXnceFcw%3D%3D_V2&jobTitle=Principal+Engineer&loc=US",
      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Provide technical leadership of  a multi-site team composed of exceptional engineering talent. \n</li>\n<li>Provide technical direction to technical leads within Analytical Storage and influence product management and technical program management teams to deliver SQL query processing for Google. \n</li>\n<li>Manage complex systems and infrastructure migrations impacting Googlers and Google products. \n</li>\n<li>Shape a multi-year technical roadmap that incorporates stakeholder priorities and charts out an ambitious plan for analytical storage (e.g., highly performant and space efficient storage formats, query capabilities, privacy policy enforcement, etc.). \n</li>\n<li>Work with other Tech Leads within Core Data and more broadly to help drive strategic technical initiatives.\n</li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering, computer science, another relevant discipline, or equivalent practical experience.\n</li>\n<li>15 years of engineering experience, or 13 years with an advanced degree.\n</li>\n<li>Experience with technical development in distributed systems and infrastructure.\n</li>\n<li>Experience in SQL and query processing at scale, including indexing and/or materialized view maintenance.\n</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Advanced degree in electrical engineering, computer science, or other relevant disciplines.\n</li>\n<li>Understanding of the technology involved in analytics (e.g., ETL, data governance, BI tools, etc.).</li>\n<li>Understanding of Google Ads technology.</li>\n<li>Ability to define and execute on a multi-year vision with incremental deliverables.</li>\n<li>Excellent customer and stakeholder management capabilities.</li>\n</ul>",
      "company_id": "companies/ebbbf0d1-8121-483c-8f99-ee92597591fc",
      "company_name": "Google",
      "language_code": "en-US",
      "locations": [
        {
          "display": "Sunnyvale, CA, USA",
          "lat": 37.4030338,
          "lon": -122.0325786,
          "address_lines": [
            "Google Building TC3, 805 11th Ave, Sunnyvale, CA 94089, USA"
          ],
          "city": "Sunnyvale",
          "post_code": "94089",
          "country": "CA",
          "country_code": "US",
          "is_remote": false
        }
      ],
      "description": "<p><b></b></p>\n<p>The analytical storage team is responsible for the systems that manage large volumes of event level data and aggregated views on top of it. Napa is Google’s exabyte-scale, multi-homed, distributed data warehouse that is optimized for high-throughput data ingestion and aggregation. Sawmill is a distributed large-scale system that allows for the collection, storage, and management of business-critical event records and makes them available for business analysis in a manner that respects our users' privacy and complies with Google policy.</p>\n\n<p>These systems underpin many of Google’s business including Google Ads, Payments, and Finance and are leveraged for a wide variety of use cases including Business Intelligence (BI) and SQL analytics, data science, and interactive analysis, real-time data serving for applications and machine learning. </p>\n\n<p>As the Uber Tech Lead for Analytical Storage, you will lead the technical roadmap. You will work closely with technical leads, engineering management, and product management to translate the roadmap into solid designs, architectures, development plans, and code. You will also have a leading role in continuing to improve the production health of the services. </p><p>The Core team builds the technical foundation behind Google’s flagship products. We are owners and advocates for the underlying design elements, developer platforms, product components, and infrastructure at Google. These are the essential building blocks for excellent, safe, and coherent experiences for our users and drive the pace of innovation for every developer. We look across Google’s products to build central solutions, break down technical barriers and strengthen existing systems. As the Core team, we have a mandate and a unique opportunity to impact important technical decisions across the company.</p>",
