      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Understand, investigate, and formulate technical roadmaps for application lifecycle platform, debugging and profiling workflows.</li>\n<li>Drive, partner with, and influence stakeholders to drive technical changes, through authoring designs, establishing core execution teams, mentoring and guiding technical leads, driving the execution of high-priority Objective Key Results, defining and improving Service-Level Agreements, and establishing metrics and success indicators.\n</li>\n<li>Contribute to the mission and development of our new product experiences through incorporating insights drawn from key technical engagements, working closely with critical customers and partners.\n</li>\n<li> Assess barriers to success, formulate plans and designs which address those needs, and influence across the organization for buy-in to those plans.</li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree in computer science, mathematics or other relevant engineering discipline, or equivalent practical experience.\n</li>\n<li>15 years of professional experience as a software engineering leader in the Infrastructure space.\n</li>\n<li>Experience with cross-functional technical innovation in engineering.\n</li>\n<li>Experience leading teams.\n</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Advanced degree in computer science, mathematics or engineering.\n</li>\n<li>Experience with ideation and innovation of technology at scale, and passion for development and the use of cross-platform shared code.\n</li>\n<li>Experience producing software products and large-scale distributed systems, delivering successfully within strict timelines.\n</li>\n<li>Understanding of computing, data centers, enterprise software, and hardware infrastructure with deep technical knowledge.\n</li>\n<li>Ability to balance detailed, technical guidance with “big picture” strategy, enabling teams to deliver products that are effective and creating new ways to manage data.\n</li>\n<li>Excellent organizational, prioritization, and written and verbal communication skills.\n</li>\n</ul>",
