      "responsibilities": "<ul>\n<li>Produce roadmaps across the technical scope, including consulting on objectives and key results across teams, reviewing designs, participating in and resolving technical discussions, and driving engineering investments for Core ML. \n</li>\n<li>Define technical goals and guide teams around technical decisions they can make, providing development support to engineers in the area. Escalate to directors or vice presidents about available team leads, resources, or challenges in development for the team. </li>\n<li>Provide leadership in critical situations or situations that require complex and immediate triaging, technical problems, other key work, and help managers of associated teams understand the larger technical issues contributing to challenges.</li>\n<li>Be an executive reviewer for changes or technical decision-making, participate in calibration and promotion feedback, and develop/drive decision making and technical review processes. </li>\n</ul>",
      "qualifications": "<p>Minimum qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>Bachelor's degree or equivalent practical experience</li>\n<li>15 years of experience working as a technical software engineering leader or 13 years with an advanced degree</li>\n<li>Experience solving problems, including applying ML to solve problems</li>\n</ul><br><p>Preferred qualifications:</p><ul>\n<li>20 years of professional experience in software engineering </li>\n<li>Experience in technical innovation in computer architecture, compiler optimization, or related fields\n</li>\n<li>Experience in reasoning and quantifying relative impacts and risks of technical work that could require the involvement of multiple engineers</li>\n<li>Understanding of responsible AI practice and experience in ML technologies</li>\n<li>Technical experience in systems and software with the leadership skills needed to influence technical leaders across the company</li>\n<li>Ability to quickly ramp up in new subject areas with short notice to guide mission-critical research into the largest potential risks related to infrastructure usage</li>\n</ul>",
